				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm pretty excited today -- my little guild and our ally guild knocked off Rydda'Dar on Wednesday night and last night, I led my first Bertox raid and we won with about a half hour to spare.  One of the key decisions I made was this:  we were pulling everything to a far south end-hallway room and killing it there.  Well, we cleared center and east king room, pulled the 12th of the kings, and my lead puller - uber-monk from Hawaii - Mookane the Magnificent - says to me, &quot;I can bring you Bert single.&quot;  Now we had planned to move to the center room to engage him, but the thought of getting him alone with zero chance of adds just seemed too good to pass up so I had him bring Bert to the room we were in.  Our main tank was a bit flustered and I admit I sprung this on her with little prep time, but we killed him fairly easily.  Just wondered, anyone else doing this?  I haven't run into anyone on Luclin who does, but that's just our server.  Anyway, all we have between us and Sol Ro Tower now is Mith Marr.</span></td>
