				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bertoxx<a name="31412"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 29 04 1:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The organization I used for this raid was kind of quirky and tailored to the specific way this cycle works.  Group 1 was the main tank group -- it has 3 warriors, a cleric, one druid with good heals and RC, and me.  I constantly twist a standard melee twist for the 3 tanks and have Aria of Asceticism handy to cure disease. Group 2 is the pull team - 3 pullers (monks and bards), a rogue to scout or drag puller corpses, and a couple of healers.  Group 3 is the rez team - another rogue, a cleric, a shaman, an enchanter, and a couple of other buff types.  Their job is specifically to get downed characters back on their feet and fully buffed asap.  Every other group is a DPS unit and I assign them to assist one of the 3 tanks.  So let's say we have 9 groups - 54 people.  Team 1 is tanks, team 2 is pullers, team 3 is rez team, teams 4 and 5 assist tank 1, teams 6 and 7 assist tank 2, teams 8 and 9 assist tank 3.  The three tanks take turns on the Adans, making sure someone has defensive up.  I am in the puller channel and advising them when the camp can handle another influx of trash mobs or a king.  We've done Bert 3 times with this structure.  The first time, another person was leading the raid and he tried to movs us right before king 12 and it was a disaster.  We screwed up and wasted 20 minutes.  The second time, we won with a half hour remaining.  The third time, the new graphics patch made Bert do some weird tricks and we wiped on the first pull.  We were beating him severely on the second pull and he despawned.  But this basic raid structure has resulted in having us basically ready to spawn Bert and pull him with about a half hour left each time.  It's embarrassing to have 30 minutes to kill him and fail, but when he's hitting your main tank from a spot 200 feet away down the hallway and out of sight of your casters, well SOE isn't exactly playing fair.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
